c0796b3e.original:
The `rl.question()` method displays the `query` by writing it to the `output`,
waits for user input to be provided on `input`, then invokes the `callback` function passing the provided input as the first argument.

When called, `rl.question()` will resume the `input` stream if it has been
paused.

If the `Interface` was created with `output` set to `null` or `undefined` the `query` is not written.

The `callback` function passed to `rl.question()` does not follow the typical
pattern of accepting an `Error` object or `null` as the first argument.
The `callback` is called with the provided answer as the only argument.

An error will be thrown if calling `rl.question()` after `rl.close()`.

Example usage:

```js
rl.question('What is your favorite food? ', (answer) => {
  console.log(`Oh, so your favorite food is ${answer}`);
});
```

Using an `AbortController` to cancel a question.

```js
const ac = new AbortController();
const signal = ac.signal;

rl.question('What is your favorite food? ', { signal }, (answer) => {
  console.log(`Oh, so your favorite food is ${answer}`);
});

signal.addEventListener('abort', () => {
  console.log('The food question timed out');
}, { once: true });

setTimeout(() => ac.abort(), 10000);
```

c0796b3e.translated:
`rl.question()` メソッドは、`query` を `output` に書き込むことで表示し、`input` でユーザー入力が提供されるのを待ち、提供された入力を第 1 引数として `callback` 関数を呼び出す。

呼び出されると、`rl.question()` は一時停止されていた `input` ストリームを再開する。

`Interface` が `output` を `null` または `undefined` に設定して作成された場合、`query` は書き込まれない。

`rl.question()` に渡される `callback` 関数は、第 1 引数として `Error` オブジェクトや `null` を受け付ける典型的なパターンには従わない。`callback` は、提供された回答を唯一の引数として呼び出される。

`rl.close()` の後に `rl.question()` を呼ぶとエラーが投げられる。

使用例:

```js
rl.question('What is your favorite food? ', (answer) => {
  console.log(`Oh, so your favorite food is ${answer}`);
});
```

`AbortController` を使って質問をキャンセルする:

```js
const ac = new AbortController();
const signal = ac.signal;

rl.question('What is your favorite food? ', { signal }, (answer) => {
  console.log(`Oh, so your favorite food is ${answer}`);
});

signal.addEventListener('abort', () => {
  console.log('The food question timed out');
}, { once: true });

setTimeout(() => ac.abort(), 10000);
```

